  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released 7/5/2018 11:30PM CT (7/6/2018 4:30 UTC)</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.4-NewItemBundlingSettings\">New Item Bundling Settings</h2><p>With this update, we are expanding bundling\u00a0beyond the strict pairing of labor/services and parts. Now you can bundle any item under a labor/service item or under a part using the following two new settings:</p><ul><li><p>Allow Bundling under\u00a0Part (as child)</p></li><li><p>Allow Bundling under Labor (as child)</p></li></ul><p><strong>What can you do with this?</strong></p><p>Now you can bundle accessories, additional labor items, or\u00a0anything else you need to track\u00a0with your labor/service charges.\u00a0You could also bundle multiple parts or consumables with a single part line item charge. You could of course do\u00a0other things with it as well, these are just a few examples!</p><p />",
